cs.DL, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.IR, cs.SD

The paper focuses on conducting a bibliometric analysis to map the spatial and temporal changes of global corporate research and development activities. This involves analyzing the number of scientific articles published by firms, which falls under the category of digital libraries (cs.DL). The analysis also involves identifying different industries and their influence on R&D performance, which could fall under social and information networks (cs.SI) and cybernetics (cs.CY). The paper also looks at spatial tendencies, which could fall under information retrieval (cs.IR) and software development (cs.SD) as these fields often involve analyzing and visualizing spatial data.
